The paper discusses security vulnerabilities in the Android stack, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a model for analyzing the cross-layer interactions in Android, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and system architecture (cs.SY). The paper specifically mentions the Android Security Framework (ASF) and the Linux kernel, which are both related to operating systems (cs.OS) and programming languages (cs.PL).
